{
  "texts": [
    "Negative stressful events in the social and family networks, such as the loss of a friend or family member, are some of the most stressful and difficult for individuals to adapt to and have the highest impact on health and wellbeing [6].Socioeconomic stress-related neighborhood factors have been shown to affect physiological stress and elevated allostatic load, which in turn impacts health disparities [7].",
    "However, the impact of stressful life events on adherence to cancer screening remains elusive.",
    "Davis et al.",
    "show that patients with anxiety, a disorder related to life stressors, are 1.7 more likely to miss mammogram screenings [8].",
    "Similarly, psychological distress has been found to negatively impact prostate cancer screening among U.S. military veterans, underscoring the role of psychological factors in preventive health behaviors [9]."
  ]
}